title: Grateful Dead Live at Indiana Convention Center on 1979-12-07
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) -> SEK'D Prodif Plus -> Samplitude Professional v7.02 -> SHN -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.03 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Don't Ease Me In-> El Paso, Big Railroad Blues, Easy To Love You-> It's All Over Now, Althea, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Eyes Of The World-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
pigpen super sad to here them say pigpen would be back, because we all know he wouldnt be back.... love pigpen ...
great show

Might have just found a 10 on scale Well I say goddamn, if this Wharf Rat is not one of the slowest, most intense versions, then I don't know jack shit.  Stole my face.  Had to listen to it several times in a row.  This is my new 10 - could've been an 11 if Donna was still in tow.  (Also it is mislabeled as being track #20 when it is actually #22, which is not Around and Around.)

2nd Set is off The tracking on this is off.  Track 13 and 14 are not the China Cat > Rider.  You have to skip to the Eyes of the World for the 2nd set to start.  After that it's straight up until you get to the end.

The quality is great in terms of recording (there is some noise in the left channel occasionally) and the playing is great, some of the '78 slowness is in evidence early on but the playing is top-notch through-ought and any real DeadHead will enjoy this thoroughly
First Show This was my first show.
